Prerequisites :
- Cordon nodes - goood practice to make nodes unscedulable any pods during upgrade
- Release notes - 1.30 - 1.31 read the docs ex - api version for ingress used to be extension/beta1 that was changed
- Start with lower Envs
- Control plane and Nodes should be of same version before the actual upgrade. if the node is one/few version behind please upgrade the node first to match with control plane.
- Also the cluster auto scaler version (if using ) should match with control plane
- At least 5 available ip adresses should be available in a subnet
-

Steps :
Eks control plan upgrade - run upgrade using eksctl upgrade --name --version
nodegroup/nodes/fargate upgrade - In ui there is an option to upgrade nodegroups using rolling update
Addones upgrade
